SELECT lc.category_name, l.lead_name, c.criteria_name FROM lead_categories lc JOIN leads l ON lc.lead_id = l.lead_id JOIN lead_criteria lc ON lc.lead_id = l.lead_id JOIN criteria c ON lc.criteria_id = c.criteria_id;

SELECT lc.criteria_name, l.lead_name FROM Criteria lc JOIN LeadCriteriaMapping lcm ON lc.criteria_id = lcm.criteria_id JOIN Leads l ON l.lead_id = lcm.lead_id WHERE lc.criteria_name LIKE '%important%';

SELECT lc.criteria_name, COUNT(lm.mapping_id) AS lead_count FROM Criteria lc LEFT JOIN LeadCriteriaMapping lm ON lc.criteria_id = lm.criteria_id GROUP BY lc.criteria_name HAVING COUNT(lm.mapping_id) > 1 ORDER BY lead_count DESC;
